Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the ginger and garlic into a #bowl{} with the @soy sauce{25%ml} and @sweet chilli sauce{32%ml}. Stir together then add the @beef strips{240%g} and stir to combine. Leave to the side to marinate while you prep the veg.

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @carrot{1} (trimmed, then halved lengthways, no need to peel). Thinly slice widthways. Trim the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Add the @egg noodle nest{2} to the boiling water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Refill your saucepan (off the heat) with cold water and pop in the noodles.

> This stops them cooking any more.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once your oil is really hot, add the steak strips (leaving any marinade in your bowl) and fry until browned on the outside, ~{2-3%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Remove the steak and any juice from the pan into a clean bowl.

Once your steak is removed from the pan, add another drizzle of @oil{} if the pan is dry, then add the pepper, carrot a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until the veggies are softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add any leftover marinade and half the spring onion to your pan, stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the steak (and any escaped juices) back in as well along with the @sesame seeds{15}, stir and cook until piping hot, ~{2%minutes}.

Drain the noodles and add them to your frying pan. Add the @ketjap manis{25%ml}, stir together and cook until the noodles are piping hot, ~{2%minutes}. Divide between your bowls and sprinkle over the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!